To use the Clafer plugin, you create a code block, like so:

````
~~~{.clafer .v .mxml}
model
~~~
````

Note that the .clafer **must** come first; the other tags are the same as in Clafer -?, except with the symbolic characters removed. This is because only alphanumeric characters function properly in the code block headers.

Test Example:

~~~{.clafer .v .k .malloy42}
telematicsSystem
    xor channel
        single
        dual

    extraDisplay ?

    xor size
        small
        large
~~~

Test Error:

~~~{.clafer .v .k}
abstract a
  this is an error
  abstract abstract
there is no way this
      is-valid#clafer!
error
~~~